79778.name: Afterlife Attendant
79778.text: Your Infuse cards also Infuse while in your deck.

79593.name: All Fel Breaks Loose

79593.flavorText: Maybe we should have made the bars closer together…

78142.name: Anima Extractor

78142.flavorText: After we are done you're welcome to help yourself to cookies and apple juice. Thank you for your donation!

79486.name: Anonymous Informant
79486.flavorText: It turns out she wasn't so great at keeping secrets after all.

78419.name: Ara'lon
78419.flavorText: If I had a nickel for every time a Hunter Legendary minion in Castle Nathria summoned three different companions, I'd have two nickels - which isn't a lot, but it's weird that it happened twice.

79538.name: Arson Accusation
79538.text: Choose a minion. Destroy it after your hero takes damage.

77482.name: Artificer Xy'mox
77482.text: Battlecry: Discover and cast a Relic. Infuse ( ): Cast all three instead.
77482.flavorText: "The anticipation to use this relic is killing me! Though, it will more likely kill you."

78375.name: Ashen Elemental
78375.text: Battlecry: Whenever your opponent draws a card next turn, they take 2 damage.
78375.flavorText: "The castle was nice but the fireplaces were too small - 2/5 stars"

79757.name: Attorney-at-Maw
79757.text: Choose One - Silence a minion; or Give a minion Immune this turn.
79757.flavorText: When the going gets tough, you don't want a criminal lawyer... you want a criminal lawyer...

76985.name: Baroness Vashj
76985.text: If this would transform into a minion, summon that minion instead.
76985.flavorText: Vashj was supposed to make an appearance in "The Sunken City," but after a freak accident in "Ashes of Outland," she ended up here.

78273.name: Batty Guest
78273.flavorText: His favorite food is chocolate cereal.

78150.name: Bibliomite
78150.text: Battlecry: Choose a card in your hand to shuffle into your deck.
78150.flavorText: He did NOT want to cast a spell.

79557.name: Bog Beast
79557.flavorText: I'm sure at least one of those bones is from an actual beast.

77300.name: Boon of the Ascended
77300.text: Give a minion +2 Health. Summon a Kyrian with its stats and Taunt.
77300.flavorText: Ascension is not some external power granted to you, it is the power you find within yourself.

78156.name: Buffet Biggun
78156.text: Battlecry: Summon two Silver Hand Recruits. Infuse ( ): Give them +2 Attack and Divine Shield.
78156.flavorText: "Look, I just want to know what kind of monster put raisins in this."

78222.name: Burden of Pride
78222.text: Summon three 1/3 Jailers with Taunt. If you have 20 or less Health, give them +1/+1.
78222.flavorText: A group of burdens is called a pride.

79770.name: Call to the Stand
79770.text: Your opponent summons a random minion from their hand.
79770.flavorText: Don't worry, there is a chair for you to sit in. It's very misleading.

76970.name: Carving Chisel
76970.text: After your hero attacks, summon a random basic Totem.
76970.flavorText: Look at your stone. Visualize the totem within. Then gently...

78418.name: Castle Kennels
78418.text: Give a friendly minion +2 Attack. If it's a Beast, give it Rush.

82310.name: Cathedral of Atonement
82310.text: Give a minion +2/+1 and draw a card.
82310.flavorText: You'll actually find more than one tonement here.

78371.name: Chatty Bartender
78371.text: At the end of your turn, if you control a Secret, deal 2 damage to all enemies.
78371.flavorText: "So a Venthyr, an Old God, and a Tauren walk into a bar…"

79602.name: Class Action Lawyer
79602.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no Neutral cards, set a minion's stats to 1/1.
79602.flavorText: "Have you or a loved one ever been injured in a Consecration?"

77370.name: Clean the Scene
77370.text: Destroy all minions with 3 or less Attack. Infuse ( ): 6 or less.
77370.flavorText: Not even the holy Light can get anima out of white silk.

79739.name: Clear Conscience
79739.text: Give a friendly minion +2/+3 and "Elusive on your opponent's turn."
79739.flavorText: Do you swear to give the buff, the whole buff, and nothing but the buff, so help you Kyrestia?

77659.name: Cold Case
77659.text: Summon two 2/2 Volatile Skeletons. Gain 4 Armor.
77659.flavorText: And that's why you keep your skeletons in your closet instead of your freezer.

84345.name: Collateral Damage
84345.text: Deal 6 damage to three random enemy minions. Excess damage hits the enemy hero.

77296.name: Conqueror's Banner
77296.text: Reveal a card from each player's deck, three times. Draw any of yours that cost more.
77296.flavorText: Olgra, I love your new tapestry! Where did you get it?

84351.name: Contract Conjurer
84351.text: Costs (3) less for each Secret you control.

76975.name: Convincing Disguise
76975.text: Transform a friendly minion into one that costs (2) more. Infuse ( ): Transform all friendly minions instead.
76975.flavorText: Okay gang, let's see who's really under the mask… *gasp* Old Man Bru'kan!?

78509.name: Convoke the Spirits
78509.text: Cast 8 random Druid spells (targets chosen randomly).
78509.flavorText: The spirits prefer to convoke when there's some hot gossip to discuss.

76968.name: Creepy Painting
76968.text: After another minion dies, become a copy of it.
76968.flavorText: I do not like this painting, Harth. Its smug aura mocks me.

79531.name: Criminal Lineup
79531.text: Choose a friendly minion. Summon 3 copies of it. Overload: (2)
79531.flavorText: Number 1, could you please sing the opening to "I Want It That Way"?

79581.name: Crooked Cook
79581.text: At the end of your turn, if you dealt 3 or more damage to the enemy hero, draw a card.
79581.flavorText: There are many things not called poison which can kill a man. But in this case, it is poison.

77428.name: Crud Caretaker
77428.flavorText: All it takes is a little love and a LOT of junk!

77525.name: Death Blossom Whomper
77525.text: Battlecry: Draw a Deathrattle minion and gain its Deathrattle.
77525.flavorText: We call her Audrey II. She was named after her mother.

79482.name: Deathborne
79482.text: Deal 2 damage to all minions. Summon a 2/2 Volatile Skeleton for each killed.
79482.flavorText: Kel'Thuzad thinks adding a silent 'e' at the end of words makes them sound cooler.

77313.name: Decimator Olgra
77313.text: Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each damaged minion, then attack all enemies.

79556.name: Defense Attorney Nathanos
79556.text: Battlecry: Discover a friendly Deathrattle minion that died this game. Gain its Deathrattle and then trigger it.
79556.flavorText: "Your Honor, my client was simply trying a new tree trimming technique!"

79990.name: Demolition Renovator
79990.flavorText: "Look, the Sire said he wanted something more open concept..."

79748.name: Dew Process
79748.text: For the rest of the game, players draw an extra card at the start of their turn.
79748.flavorText: All part of dewing your dew diligence.

79992.name: Dinner Performer
79992.text: Battlecry: Summon a random minion from your deck that you can afford to play.

78117.name: Dispose of Evidence
78117.text: Give your hero +3 Attack this turn. Choose a card in your hand to shuffle into your deck.
78117.flavorText: Just because you did it doesn't mean you have to be guilty.

75876.name: Dispossessed Soul
75876.text: Battlecry: If you control a location, Discover a copy of a card in your deck.
75876.flavorText: I'm afraid it came as a great shock to her when she died.

78085.name: Divine Toll
78085.text: Shoot 5 rays at random minions. They give friendly minions +2/+2, and deal 2 damage to enemy minions.
78085.flavorText: Never send to know for whom the bell tolls.

77556.name: Door of Shadows
77556.text: Draw a spell. Infuse ( ): Add a Temporary copy of it to your hand.
77556.flavorText: Upon arrival, please ring the doorbell of shadows, and wipe your shoes on the doormat of shadows before entering.

77148.name: Double Cross
77148.text: Secret: When your opponent spends all their Mana, draw two cards.
77148.flavorText: Valeera revealed herself to be a double agent. At which point Maiev felt comfortable revealing that she also was a double agent. And then Scabbs announced to everybody that - get this - he was a double agent.

78373.name: Dredger Staff
78373.text: Battlecry: Give minions in your hand +1 Health.
78373.flavorText: The dredger staff held the dredger knife and said, "Dredger bow before the Sire!"

78393.name: Elitist Snob
78393.text: Battlecry: For each Paladin card in your hand, randomly gain Divine Shield, Lifesteal, Rush, or Taunt.
78393.flavorText: "I heard the Sire invited a Murloc! How dreadful!"

79932.name: Famished Fool
79932.flavorText: He's not hungry for food, he's starving for attention!

77057.name: Flustered Librarian
77057.text: Has +1 Attack for each Imp you control.

79784.name: Forensic Duster
79784.text: Battlecry: Your opponent's minions cost (1) more next turn.
79784.flavorText: He had plenty of experience with dusting things from his time as a butler, so when a murder was committed he saw a real job opportunity!

77033.name: Framester
77033.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 3 'Framed' cards into the opponent's deck. When drawn, they Overload for (2).
77033.flavorText: "Who put these beans in my pocket?!" -Man With Beans in Pocket

84354.name: Frozen Touch
84354.text: Deal 3 damage. Infuse ( ): Add a Frozen Touch to your hand.
84354.flavorText: Is this what Bob was talking about when he said he served a drink to a Death Knight once?

78275.name: Ghastly Gravedigger
78275.text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, choose a card in your opponent's hand to shuffle into their deck.
78275.flavorText: Some people take their secrets to the grave.

78525.name: Gigantotem
78525.text: Costs (1) less for each Totem you've summoned this game.
78525.flavorText: Totem Golem's uncle, gone too soon.

82316.name: Great Hall
82316.text: Set a minion's Attack and Health to 3.
82316.flavorText: It's fabulous! It's grand! It's, well it's really very nice.

79540.name: Habeas Corpses
79540.text: Discover a friendly minion to resurrect and give it Rush. It dies at the end of turn.

77152.name: Halkias
77152.text: Stealth. Deathrattle: Store Halkias's soul inside of a friendly Secret. It resummons Halkias when triggered.
77152.flavorText: Everybody tough until the sinstones start walking.

78202.name: Hedge Maze
78202.flavorText: If you keep seeing a statue of the Sire, you’re not going in circles. There’s just so many of them.

78270.name: Huntsman Altimor
78270.text: Battlecry: Summon a Gargon Companion. Infuse ( ): Summon another. Infuse ( ): And another!
78270.flavorText: He loves all his Gargons equally. (Hecutis is his favorite and it's not close.)

77368.name: Identity Theft
77368.text: Discover a copy of a card from your opponent's hand and deck.
77368.flavorText: Identity theft is not a joke, Jim!

77311.name: Imbued Axe
77311.text: After your hero attacks, give your damaged minions +1/+2. Infuse ( ): +2/+2 instead.

78363.name: Imp King Rafaam
78363.text: Battlecry: Resurrect four friendly Imps. Infuse ( ): Give your Imps +2/+2.
78363.flavorText: Not even death can stop Rafaam from pursuing a life of crime.

79537.name: Imp-oster
79537.text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly Imp. Transform into a copy of it.
79537.flavorText: There is an imposter among us.

77055.name: Impending Catastrophe
77055.text: Draw a card. Repeat for each Imp you control.
77055.flavorText: The imps end you, and the cats... well, they astrophe.

77488.name: Incarceration

79742.name: Incriminating Psychic

79742.flavorText: Good news: He knows Kazakus's secret identity! Bad news: Now he's here.

79584.name: Insatiable Devourer
79584.text: Battlecry: Devour an enemy minion and gain its stats. Infuse ( ): And its neighbors.
79584.flavorText: You're not you when you're anima-starved.

79535.name: Invitation Courier

79535.flavorText: Sending mail via steward is soooo old school.

78145.name: Jury Duty
78145.text: Summon two Silver Hand Recruits. Give your Silver Hand Recruits +1/+1.
78145.flavorText: The most criminal thing about paladins is that they actually like jury duty.

79934.name: Kael'thas Sinstrider
79934.text: Every third minion you play each turn costs (0).
79934.flavorText: You heard about Kael'thas? That's messed up, right?

78394.name: Kel'Thuzad, the Inevitable
78394.text: Battlecry: Resurrect your Volatile Skeletons. Any that can't fit on the battlefield instantly explode! ( )
78394.flavorText: Looks like Kel'Thuzad is borrowing some of Mr. Bigglesworth's nine lives.

77151.name: Kidnap

78125.name: Kryxis the Voracious
78125.flavorText: Tried intermittent fasting. It didn't stick.

79111.name: Lady Darkvein

79111.flavorText: You're so vein. I bet you think this flavor text is about you.

79596.name: Life Sentence
79596.text: Remove a minion from the game.
79596.flavorText: Also sentenced to laugh and love.

78123.name: Magnifying Glaive
78123.text: After your hero attacks, draw until you have 3 cards.

79563.name: Masked Reveler

79563.flavorText: "It's party time! P-A-R-T-Why? Because I gotta!"

79771.name: Mawsworn Bailiff

79771.flavorText: Bailiff, bring in the dancing lobsters!

77491.name: Maze Guide
77491.flavorText: "And if you look to your left, you'll see an even larger statue of Sire Denathrius!"

77056.name: Mischievous Imp
77056.text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of this. Infuse ( ): Summon two copies instead.
77056.flavorText: Why is it when something happens, it is always you three?

79555.name: Motion Denied
79555.text: Secret: After your opponent plays three cards in a turn, deal 6 damage to the enemy hero.
79555.flavorText: DO NOT PASS GO. DO NOT COLLECT 200 GOLD.

78133.name: Muck Plumber
78133.flavorText: If you drink muck, you go to the Maw before you die.

76981.name: Muck Pools
76981.text: Transform a friendly minion into one that costs (1) more.
76981.flavorText: Making a dredger is easier than you'd think. You don't need to worry about mucking it up!

78080.name: Muckborn Servant
78080.flavorText: Party guests never tip as well as the patrons in Bob's tavern.

79608.name: Murder Accusation
79608.text: Choose a minion. Destroy it after another enemy minion dies.
79608.flavorText: Quote From Man Murdered: "What are you gonna do, murder me?"

79935.name: Murloc Holmes
79935.text: Battlecry: Solve 3 Clues about your opponent's cards to get copies of them.
79935.flavorText: When you have eliminated the imfroggable, whatever remains, however uncroakable, must be the truth.

78155.name: Murlocula

77298.name: Mysterious Visitor
77298.text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of cards copied from your opponent by (3).
77298.flavorText: Dave, we can tell this letter is fake - it's in your handwriting. And take off that stupid hood, you're embarrassing us.

77490.name: Natural Causes

77558.name: Necrolord Draka
77558.text: Battlecry: Equip a /3 Dagger. (+1 Attack for each other card you played this turn!)
77558.flavorText: We originally planned on giving Rogue a Legendary minion called "The Moon", but SOMEONE jumped in the frame.

84356.name: Nightcloak Sanctum
84356.text: Freeze a minion. Summon a 2/2 Volatile Skeleton.

77562.name: Nightshade Bud
77562.text: Choose One - Discover a minion from your deck to summon; or a spell to cast.
77562.flavorText: It actually thrives in partial sunlight.

79548.name: Objection!
79548.text: Secret: When your opponent plays a minion, Counter it.

78144.name: Order in the Court
78144.text: Reorder your deck from highest Cost to lowest Cost.
78144.flavorText: "I have nothing BUT contempt for this court!"

78397.name: Orion, Mansion Manager
78397.text: After a friendly Secret is revealed, cast a different Mage Secret and gain +2/+2.
78397.flavorText: The secrets of the universe are vast... and will be revealed sometime later this game.

77299.name: Partner in Crime
77299.text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of this minion at the end of your turn.
77299.flavorText: "You know what we need? Some rope." "That's stupid. Name one thing you'd need a rope for."

78547.name: Party Crasher
78547.text: Battlecry: Choose an enemy minion. Throw a random minion from your hand at it.
78547.flavorText: "Do you ever wonder why you don't get invited anywhere?" "… no, not really."

77366.name: Party Favor Totem
77366.text: At the end of your turn, summon a random basic Totem. Infuse ( ): Summon two instead.
77366.flavorText: It's the gift (totem) that keeps on giving (totems)!

77306.name: Pelagos
77306.text: After you cast a spell on a friendly minion, set its Attack and Health to the higher of the two.
77306.flavorText: He's a great judge of character.

79607.name: Perjury
79607.text: Secret: When your turn starts, Discover and cast a Secret from another class.

77654.name: Planted Evidence
77654.text: Discover a spell. It costs (2) less this turn.
77654.flavorText: So you're telling me this wasn't Natural Causes?

78261.name: Plot of Sin
78261.text: Summon two 2/2 Treants. Infuse ( ): Two 5/5 Ancients instead.
78261.flavorText: It's a great plot, but it's riddled with holes.

78153.name: Priest of the Deceased
78153.flavorText: "Funnel cakes? I haven't had those in years…"

76982.name: Primordial Wave
76982.text: Transform enemy minions into ones that cost (1) less and friendly minions into ones that cost (1) more.
76982.flavorText: A primordial hello to you too!

79767.name: Prince Renathal
79767.text: Your deck size and starting Health are 40.
79767.flavorText: A lot of kids go through a rebellious phase, but Prince Renathal's was a bit extreme.

77149.name: Private Eye
77149.text: Battlecry: Cast a Secret from your deck. Combo: Cast 2 instead.
77149.flavorText: Eye see what you did there.

79741.name: Promotion
79741.text: Give a Silver Hand Recruit +3/+3 and Taunt.
79741.flavorText: And with the new title of 'Golden Hand Recruit', you also get a pay raise!

79598.name: Prosecutor Mel'tranix
79598.text: Battlecry: Your opponent can only play their left- and right-most cards on their next turn.
79598.flavorText: "Your Honor. The Defense isn't a clown, he's the whole circus."

79562.name: Red Herring
79562.flavorText: He's got gill-ty written all over him!

77615.name: Relic Vault
77615.text: The next Relic you play this turn casts twice.
77615.flavorText: Holds Sire Denathrius' most prized possession - his teddy bear, Jeremy Bearimy.

78122.name: Relic of Dimensions
78122.text: Draw two cards and reduce their Cost by ( ). Improve your future Relics.
78122.flavorText: A glaive is a glaive, but a mystery box could be anything! It could even be a glaive!

78469.name: Relic of Extinction
78469.text: Deal damage to a random enemy minion, twice. Improve your future Relics.
78469.flavorText: Faster than an asteroid, and just as effective.

77616.name: Relic of Phantasms
77616.text: Summon two / Spirits. Improve your future Relics.
77616.flavorText: Xy'mox chuckled. "You mean the Chaos Emerald?"

77704.name: Remornia, Living Blade
77704.flavorText: Was it the lead pipe... the candlestick... or the unhinged, sentient, bloodthirsty sword?

78262.name: Riot!
78262.text: Your minions can't be reduced below 1 Health this turn. They each attack a random enemy minion.

82313.name: Sanguine Depths
82313.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
82313.flavorText: There may not be any skeletons in the closets at Castle Nathria, but there sure are souls in the basement.

79612.name: Scribbling Stenographer
79612.text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each card you've played this turn.
79612.flavorText: A truly staggering 180 scribbles per minute!

75868.name: Scuttlebutt Ghoul
75868.text: Taunt Battlecry: If you control a Secret, summon a copy of this.

77557.name: Serrated Bone Spike
77557.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. If it dies, your next card this turn costs (2) less.
77557.flavorText: Draka, in an attempt to help, threw them a bone.

78081.name: Service Bell
78081.text: Discover a Class card from your deck and draw all copies of it.
78081.flavorText: The bell tolls for us! Waiter, we need more water!

78383.name: Sesselie of the Fae Court
78383.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Draw a minion. Reduce its Cost by (8).
78383.flavorText: They claim they're from the Fae Court, but that might be a Fae Kout.

79552.name: Shadehound
79552.text: Whenever this attacks, give your other Beasts +2/+2. Infuse ( Beasts): Gain Rush.
79552.flavorText: This Shadehound wasn't just a good boy. He was the best.

79108.name: Shadow Waltz
79108.text: Summon a 3/5 Shadow with Taunt. If a minion died this turn, summon another.
79108.flavorText: They're dancing to one of Rin's demonic symphonies. Her music might not be famous now, but just you wait!

79142.name: Shadowborn
79142.text: Deathrattle: Reduce the Cost of the highest Cost Shadow spell in your hand by (3).
79142.flavorText: You merely adopted the shadows; I was born in them!

79549.name: Sightless Magistrate
79549.text: Battlecry: Both players draw until they have 5 cards.
79549.flavorText: Does "Justice is Blind" still apply with Spectral Sight?

79928.name: Sinfueled Golem
79928.text: Infuse ( ): Gain stats equal to the Attack of the minions that Infused this.
79928.flavorText: That poor golem is going to be stuck as a guard forever. He can never get a head!

78111.name: Sinful Brand
78111.text: Brand an enemy minion. Whenever it takes damage, deal 1 damage to the enemy hero.

78143.name: Sinful Sous Chef
78143.text: Deathrattle: Add 2 Silver Hand Recruits to your hand.
78143.flavorText: If this dinner party goes well, she thinks she has a good shot at being on Fel's Kitchen.

77308.name: Sinrunner
77308.flavorText: Blanchy was said to be an affectionate and well-behaved horse in life. How she ended up in Revendreth? We're too afraid to ask.

82369.name: Sinstone Graveyard
82369.text: Summon a / Ghost. (Has +1/+1 for each other card you played this turn!)
82369.flavorText: A graveyard in the realm of the dead; a bit redundant, don't you think?

78532.name: Sinstone Totem
78532.text: At the end of your turn, gain +1 Health.
78532.flavorText: This one's heavier than the wooden totems. Mostly from the weight of your sins.

75881.name: Sire Denathrius
75881.text: Lifesteal. Battlecry: Deal 5 damage amongst enemies. Endlessly Infuse ( ): Deal 1 more.
75881.flavorText: History has a way of altering villains so that we can no longer see ourselves in them. Unfortunately for the Venthyr, they all look like Sire Denathrius.

77714.name: Sketchy Stranger
77714.flavorText: More of a 'Painted Stranger' if you ask me.

77642.name: Solid Alibi
77642.text: Until your next turn, your hero can only take 1 damage at a time.

79546.name: Soul Seeker
79546.text: Battlecry: Swap this with a random minion from your opponent's deck.
79546.flavorText: The Soul Seeker's job is to look for a snitch.

78412.name: Spirit Poacher
78412.flavorText: Always poach from your local spirit shelter.

78420.name: Stag Charge
78420.text: Deal 3 damage. Summon a random Dormant Wildseed.

78079.name: Steamcleaner
78079.text: Battlecry: Destroy ALL cards in both players' decks that didn't start there.
78079.flavorText: Business is slow since the anima shortage began. Things just don't get stained like they used to!

78146.name: Stewart the Steward
78146.text: Deathrattle: Give the next Silver Hand Recruit you summon +3/+3 and this Deathrattle.
78146.flavorText: How many bites does it take to get the center of an hors d'oeuvre?

77150.name: Sticky Situation
77150.text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, summon a 3/4 Spider with Stealth.
77150.flavorText: "Now this is what I'd call..." "...just shut up."

79532.name: Stoneborn General
79532.flavorText: Leads with an iron fist and a stony demeanor.

78268.name: Stonebound Gargon
78268.text: Rush Infuse ( ): Also damages the minions next to whomever this attacks.

76922.name: Suffocating Shadows
76922.text: When you play or discard this, destroy a random enemy minion.
76922.flavorText: "Reading is good for you," they said.

75866.name: Suspicious Alchemist
75866.text: Battlecry: Discover a spell. If your opponent guesses your choice, they get a copy.
